=========================================================
  rails_ai_build installed!

  Next steps:

  1. Run migrations:
       rails db:migrate

  2. Set an API key (any one is enough):

       # NVIDIA NIM (free tier at https://build.nvidia.com)
       export NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-...
       # optional model override:
       export NVIDIA_MODEL=meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct

       # or OpenAI / Anthropic
       export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
       export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

     Keys can also be set in config/initializers/rails_ai_build.rb.
     When NVIDIA_API_KEY is set, the gem defaults to :nvidia automatically.

  3. The engine is mounted at /rails_ai_build (disable auto_mount to change).

  4. Create an agent via API or console:

       # Uses default provider (nvidia if NVIDIA_API_KEY is set)
       agent = RailsAiBuild::Agents::Agent.new
       result = agent.chat("Add a health check endpoint to config/routes.rb")

       # Or force NVIDIA explicitly
       agent = RailsAiBuild::Agents::Agent.new(
         provider: :nvidia,
         model: "meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct"
       )

  See README for full documentation.
